name: Final Fantasy Annual 2018-2020 Original Illustration Art Book.
cleanName: Final Fantasy Annual 2018 2020 Original Illustration Art Book
extDescription:
Introducing a new art book containing magnificent original illustrations created for the FINAL FANTASY TRADING CARD GAME!
Includes all FFTCG original card illustrations from Opus IV through Opus XII: Crystal Awakening, as well as original promotional artwork created for FFTCG events!
Additionally, you can find a series of interviews held with a total of 12 illustrators, which garnered a very positive response when shown on the FINAL FANTASY PORTAL SITE, as well as the results of the 2018 and 2019 World Championships.
Also, as a bonus, the book comes with three copies of an exclusive promo card, “Clan Gully [PR-085]” featuring the main cast of FINAL FANTASY TACTICS ADVANCE 2. This card is special, as the art was originally created to promote FINAL FANTASY TCG events, and was illustrated by Final Fantasy series veteran, Ryoma Ito!
This collection contains approximately 100 pieces of beautifully illustrated art and celebrates the legacy of the FINAL FANTASY TRADING CARD GAME thus far. Excellent for any FINAL FANTASY fan!
Item Info:
Page Count: 144 pages
Trim Size: A4 (w 22 cm x h 30 cm, thickness 1.4cm)
Format: Soft cover
Text: Japanese/English

name: Final Fantasy Annual Special PR Card Collection Noir
cleanName: Final Fantasy Annual Special PR Card Collection Noir
extDescription:
FINAL FANTASY TRADING CARD GAME SPECIAL PR CARD COLLECTION Noir is a set of specially designed FFTCG cards featuring characters from FINAL FANTASY VII. Enclosed in a two-page album, commemorating the 25th anniversary of FINAL FANTASY VII, a total of 12 cards can be found in a two-page spread. Each card in the set has been boldly redesigned with a different color scheme and a monochromatic color palette with one accent color, plus they are foil-stamped with Tetsuya Nomura’s autograph. The product, along with the album design, exudes a mature, relaxed, and luxurious feel.
12 cards are enclosed in a two-page spread.
The promotional cards are specially designed with a monochromatic version of existing cards. All cards are foil-stamped with Tetsuya Nomura's autograph.
